topic.title: PMON

li.p: Provides IEEE 802.3 clause 30: basic, mandatory and recommended packages.
Provides RFC 2665 (MIB), RFC 2635 (updated for SNMP) statistics.
Provides enhanced PMON for transmit MAC.
Provides saturating statistic counters for accumulation up to one second.
Provides manual transfer of statistics counters into holding registers.
Provides optional automatic transfer of statistic counters into holding registers from an external one second period latch event.

body.p: The ENET subsystem provides the following statistic counters:

entry.p: Per PCS virtual lane count of received BIP errors (100GE).
Per FEC lane count of received and corrected FEC errors.
Per FEC lane count of received and uncorrected FEC errors.
Per link count of received scrambled idle test pattern error count.
Per channel count of loss of block lock events (LOBL).
Virtual Lane loss of block lock count
Per PCS virtual lane count of loss of block lock events (LOBL).
Per channel FEC symbol error count

row.entry: SERDES lane FEC symbol error count

entry.p: Per SERDES lane FEC symbol error count
Per link Count of received block errors including:
(3) 66-bit blocks with invalid block type field

All octets received except preamble (i.e. Header, Payload, Padding and FCS) for all valid frames and valid pause frames received.

Incremented with each valid frame received on the Receive FIFO interface and all bits of the destination address were set to '1'.
Total number of packets received. Good and bad packets.
Total number of octets received. Good and bad packets.
Total number of frames received with invalid preamble. Any occurrence with START character on Byte 0 of GMII column not followed by six bytes of 0x55 and one byte 0xD5 (SFD) on byte 7.

body.p: The following PCS Ethernet statistics for the transmit path are provided in the MAPOTN subsystem and not the ENET subsystem:

entry.p: Per lane count of received BIP errors.
Count number of test pattern errors. Only 1 channel at a time.
Per link Count of received block errors including:
(3) 66-bit blocks with invalid block type field
Per link count of received sync header errors.
Per link count of received /E/ characters
Per link count of received control codewords with unknown block type.
Per link count of block syn events.
Per link count of packet discarded because their length is smaller than the minimum configured packet length
